org.apache.xerces.impl

Interface XMLDocumentFragmentScannerImpl.Dispatcher

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    XML11NSDocumentScannerImpl.NS11ContentDispatcher, XMLDocumentFragmentScannerImpl.FragmentContentDispatcher, XMLDocumentScannerImpl.ContentDispatcher, XMLDocumentScannerImpl.DTDDispatcher, XMLDocumentScannerImpl.PrologDispatcher, XMLDocumentScannerImpl.TrailingMiscDispatcher, XMLDocumentScannerImpl.XMLDeclDispatcher, XMLNSDocumentScannerImpl.NSContentDispatcher
    Enclosing class:
    XMLDocumentFragmentScannerImpl

    protected static interface XMLDocumentFragmentScannerImpl.Dispatcher
    This interface defines an XML "event" dispatching model. Classes that implement this interface are responsible for scanning parts of the XML document and dispatching callbacks.
    Author:
    Glenn Marcy, IBM

    INTERNAL:

    Usage of this class is not supported. It may be altered or removed at any time.

    • Method Detail

      • dispatch

        boolean dispatch(boolean complete)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        org.apache.xerces.xni.XNIException
        Dispatch an XML "event".
        Parameters:
        complete - True if this dispatcher is intended to scan and dispatch as much as possible.
        Returns:
        True if there is more to dispatch either from this or a another dispatcher.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Thrown on i/o error.
        org.apache.xerces.xni.XNIException - Thrown on parse error.
